  "prompt": "What are the new features in iPhone 7?",
  "response": "While the iPhone 7 is a bit older now, it introduced some notable features at the time. Here's a rundown of what was new:\n\n**Key New Features:**\n\n*   **Water and Dust Resistance:** The iPhone 7 was the first iPhone to have an official IP67 rating for water and dust resistance. This meant it could withstand splashes, spills, and even being submerged in shallow water for a short period.\n\n*   **Improved Camera:**\n    *   **12MP Rear Camera:** Featuring a larger aperture (\u0192/1.8) for better low-light performance.\n    *   **Optical Image Stabilization (OIS):**  Reduced blurring from shaky hands, resulting in sharper photos and videos.\n    *   **7MP Front Camera:** Upgraded from the 5MP camera in previous models, offering better selfies.\n\n*   **New Colors:** Introduced new color options, including:\n    *   **Matte Black:** A sleek, understated black finish.\n    *   **Jet Black:** A high-gloss, piano-black finish (this one was more prone to scratching).\n\n*   **A10 Fusion Chip:** A new quad-core processor that offered significantly faster performance and improved energy efficiency compared to the A9 chip in the iPhone 6s.\n\n*   **Stereo Speakers:**  The iPhone 7 featured stereo speakers for the first time, with one speaker at the bottom and another in the earpiece, providing a wider soundstage.\n\n*   **Home Button Redesign (Solid-State):** The traditional clicky Home button was replaced with a solid-state button that used the Taptic Engine to simulate the feeling of a click. It was pressure-sensitive and customizable.\n\n*   **No Headphone Jack:** The most controversial change was the removal of the 3.5mm headphone jack. Apple included Lightning EarPods and a Lightning-to-3.5mm adapter in the box, but the change was still met with resistance.\n\n**Other Improvements:**\n\n*   **Brighter Display:** The Retina HD display was brighter than previous models, offering better visibility in sunlight.\n*   **Faster LTE:**  Improved LTE speeds for faster downloads and browsing.\n*   **More Storage Options:** Offered larger storage capacities, up to 256GB.\n\nKeep in mind that technology has advanced significantly since the iPhone 7's release, so many of these features are now standard on newer smartphones and have been surpassed by more advanced technologies.",
